@model KillBoardViewModel
<div class="bg-img bg-img-2"></div>
<h2>Kill Count</h2>
<div>
    <blockquote>
        (<a href="#open-modal-bugs">why are they attacking eachother?</a>)
    </blockquote>
</div>
<div class="split left">
    <blockquote>
        <p>Top 5 most destructive robots</p>
        <ol>
            @foreach (var robot in Model.Robots)
            {
                <li><a href="#open-modal-detail" data-id="@robot.Id"><strong>@robot.Name</strong></a> has destroyed <strong>@robot.KillCount</strong> units!</li>
            }
        </ol>
    </blockquote>
</div>
<div class="split right">
    <blockquote>
        <p>Top 5 destructive cyborgs</p>
        <ol>
            @foreach (var cyborg in Model.Cyborgs)
            {
                <li><a href="#open-modal-detail" data-id="@cyborg.Id"><strong>@cyborg.Name</strong></a> has destroyed <strong>@cyborg.KillCount</strong> units!</li>
            }
        </ol>
    </blockquote>
</div>

<div id="open-modal-bugs" class="modal-window" style="z-index: 1001;">
    <div style="z-index: 1001;width: 60%;top: 40%;">
        <a href="#" title="Close" class="modal-close">Close (esc)</a>

        <div>
            <p>So why are the robots attacking eachother from time to time? Well...</p>
            <br />
            <p>No one really knows for sure. Some say <a target="_blank" style="color: blue;" href="https://www.lifewire.com/thmb/3KHFRyRmvqVKURMwfA0Viii9LEg=/1600x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc():format(webp)/aliens1-5ad5062f3037130037462d1c.jpg">aliens</a>...</p>
            <br />
            <p>
                But we here at YourBestRoboticsCyborgsAndMoreManufacturingAndProgrammingNeedsForeverResolved.inc we believe its because of bugs.
            </p>
            <br />
            <p>
                A bug is a technical term in programaniese that expresses the idea of 'faulty code', or code that is a 'candidate for optimization', or simply an 'unexpected feature'!
            </p>
            <br />
            <p>
                We prefer the latter definition here at YourBestRoboticsCyborgsAndMoreManufacturingAndProgrammingNeedsForeverResolved.inc.
            </p>
            <br />
            <p>
                Sometimes the bot may... "misinterpret" your request. So instead of "Sweep the House!", it may prefer "Set the house on fire!".
            </p>
            <br />
            <p>
                Or, instead of "Wash the Car!", it may plant C4 in your neighbors car. In any case, other robots may be damaged in the process.
            </p>
            <br />
            <p>
                With the trillions of lines of code that goes into every made-with-love bot, its likely our sole developer missed a semicolon somewhere.
            </p>
            <br />
            <p>
                But worry not! Any damages occured will be billed to {place_fake_insurance_company_here} and covered by them!
            </p>
            <br />
            <br />
            <p>
                Sincerely,
            </p>
            <br />
            <p>
                YourBestRoboticsCyborgsAndMoreManufacturingAndProgrammingNeedsForeverResolved.inc
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>